Due to the school closures and the inability to reach out through a flyer, Girl Scouts has asked us to share the following information. Please contact them directly, as this is not a school sponsored organization. Thanks!

Calling all girls from Pre-K through 5th grade...

Girl Scouts is a magical place of FUN, FRIENDS & ADVENTURES! Though we may be experiencing a difficult time right now, Girl Scouts would like to invite you to get engaged and inspired with us. We’ve got fun virtual activities now to give her a taste of what is to come when troops start to form later this summer. Learn more about becoming a Girl Scout at www.gsksmo.org/newmember.

post_text: Our lunch prep staff have been amazing!! Thank you ladies for all you do!
shared_text:
Missouri Department of Elementary and Secondary Education
May 1 at 7:00 AM ·

Today, we celebrate "School Lunch Hero Day!" Between preparing healthy food, adhering to strict nutrition standards, navigating student food allergies, and offering service with a smile, Missouri nutrition professionals have a lot on their plate on a “normal” day. Extended building closures during COVID-19 required our food service professionals to quickly be innovative and creative to develop ways to continue feeding the Missouri students who rely on school breakfast and lunch each day.

Join us in recognizing these important team members today!

Our lunch prep staff have been amazing!! Thank you ladies for all you do!

shared_text:
Husker Library Page
April 19 at 10:03 PM ·

Favorite Book Character Challenge-
It is National Library Week!
If you were at Grandview last year, you might remember our favorite book character potato challenge. This year, I am challenging you to create your favorite book character out of whatever you wish. It can be done on paper, created from clay, legos, food items, or anything you can get your hands on and want to use. Email photos of your character to Mrs. Bell (bellc@huskersk12.org) or post in the comments here. There will be a winner from PK-2 and 3-5 just like last year as well as a Middle School, High School and an adult winner. Have fun and keep reading!

Last years winners-Harry Potter and Hedwig the Owl

post_text:
Hello parents,

We wanted to update you on several items as we end this first week being absent from school.

For our district, our priority is the safety of students, staff, and the community. That priority is how we are making all other decisions. With that being said, starting next week, staff will reach out through electronic communication and provide learning materials, opportunities, and resources to students in order to maintain their essential skills while we are on this break.

Also, next week there will be a small change to our meal distribution. In order to minimize social contact, meals will be provided once a day and will include both lunch and breakfast. The schedule will be as follows.

Monday, 3/23 - 8:00 - 9:00, breakfast will be available. Then from 11:00 - 12:00, Monday lunch and Tuesday breakfast will both be served together

Each day thereafter, from 11:00 - 12:00, that day's lunch and the next day's breakfast will be provided during one pick-up time.

Please continue to practice safe hygiene and social distancing and stay healthy!

Also, next week there will be a small change to our meal distribution. In order to minimize social contact, meals will be provided once a day and will include both lunch and breakfast. The schedule will be as follows.

Monday, 3/23 - 8:00 - 9:00, breakfast will be available. Then from 11:00 - 12:00, Monday lunch and Tuesday breakfast will both be served together

Each day thereafter, from 11:00 - 12:00, that day's lunch and the next day's breakfast will be provided during one pick-up time.

Please continue to practice safe hygiene and social distancing and stay healthy!

post_text:
Starting Tuesday, March 17th, our district will be serving grab-n-go breakfast and lunch. Breakfast will be served between 8:00 and 9:00 am and lunch is served between 11:00 and 12:00 pm. Pick up locations will be Grandview Elementary (under the preschool awning), Grace UMC parking lot (15th and Main, Higginsville), and City of Corder City Hall. This will be on weekdays only. No cost to anyone under 18 and to adults with disabilities under 21.

If parents need access to medications stored at school, the nurses office at GV and MS/HS will be open on Tuesday, March 17th, from 12-4 pm for medication pick up.

Grades are postponed for the time being; no end of quarter due dates yet.

If you have questions or concerns, you may contact the district office at (660)584-3631. #GVElemrocks
